sentences: Beverley Martyn (born Beverley Kutner on 24 March 1947) is an English singer, songwriter and guitarist.
She appeared in the photograph on the album sleeve of Bert Jansch's 1965 album, It Don't Bother Me, where she can be seen lounging in the background.
"Babe I'm Leaving You", which was released on the Parlophone label in 1965.

In 1966 she released a single, "Happy New Year" (b-side "Where The Good Times Are"), written by Randy Newman, on which she was accompanied by Jimmy Page, John Paul Jones, Nicky Hopkins and Andy White.

In 1966 she released a single, "Happy New Year" (b-side "Where The Good Times Are"), written by Randy Newman, on which she was accompanied by Jimmy Page, John Paul Jones, Nicky Hopkins and Andy White.
"Happy New Year" was chosen as the first single release on the brand new Deram label, distributed by Decca Records, in 1966, catalogue number DM 101.

She also recorded a then unreleased single in the same year, "Picking Up The Sunshine" / "Gin House Blues".
The single was released in April 2017.
Her follow-up single "Museum", written by Donovan and produced by Denny Cordell, was released in 1967.
On the Simon & Garfunkel album Bookends, she contributed to the track "Fakin' It", in the middle of which she is heard saying: "Good morning, Mr Leitch, have you had a busy day?"

She later appeared at the Monterey Pop Festival on 16 June 1967, as did Simon & Garfunkel.
In 1969, she met John Martyn, whom she later married.
The couple divorced during the making of John Martyn's album Grace and Danger in 1980 and she retired from music for years.

In the 1990s, with her children now grown, she was invited to join Loudon Wainwright III on his European tour.

In 1998 she resumed her recording career with the release of the album No Frills.

In 2004, Martyn's song "Primrose Hill", about the simple joys of domesticity, which she wrote and sang on Road To Ruin, was sampled by Fat Boy Slim for the track "North West Three" on his 2004 album Palookaville.

In 2004, Martyn's song "Primrose Hill", about the simple joys of domesticity, which she wrote and sang on Road To Ruin, was sampled by Fat Boy Slim for the track "North West Three" on his 2004 album Palookaville.

On 3 December 2013, she performed the song "Levee Breaks" with her band at the concert 'A Celebration Of Bert Jansch' at London's Royal Festival Hall, alongside Robert Plant, Donovan and various members of Pentangle, amongst others.
The concert was broadcast by BBC4 in the UK on 28 March 2014 under the name The Genius of Bert Jansch: Folk Blues and Beyond.
Martyn released a new album in 2014 entitled The Phoenix and The Turtle.
It contains a previously unrecorded Nick Drake and Martyn song, "Reckless Jane".
